comments: Holmgren (OKC) briefly places both hands on Jones Jr. (DAL) before he releases away to roll to the basket.
Washington (DAL) holds down Williams' (OKC) shoulder as he jumps to contest and the illegal contact affects Williams' driving shot attempt.
Williams' (OKC) shot attempt makes contact with the bottom of the backboard and goes out of bounds.  Washington (DAL) never makes contact with the ball and possession should be given to Dallas.
Jones Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in Williams' (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Holmgren (OKC) legally contests Jones Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Washington (DAL) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests Washington's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Washington (DAL) extends a hand into Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) front, affecting his SQBR.
Washington (DAL) runs into Dort (OKC) and dislodges him from his legally obtained screening position.
Jones Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Dort (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position defending Doncic (DAL) on the perimeter.  When Doncic backs down Dort in the lane, Dort reaches in and any contact with Doncic's arm is marginal.

Replay review of the foul called on Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Although Gilgeous-Alexander initially makes contact with the ball, he does not dislodge it from Washington's (DAL) control and continues to slide down to Washington's arm while he is in a shooting motion making the arm contact illegal.
Morris (DAL) legally contests Williams' (OKC) jump shot attempt.
